I have finally decided to read a book by bell hooks. And let me tell you, I'm loving it! I chose All About Love. (I'm a polyamorist. Could you have expected otherwise?) And this passage stuck out to me. It reminded me how, to avoid conflict, some will say, I don't want you to change for me. I feel there's a similarity. Why is asking for change so taboo? Especially when it's the others choice to change or not. Love is transformative. We are meant to change.
